# Global Project Rules - StudySprint

## JavaScript Style

- **No semicolons** (unless required to disambiguate)
- **Single quotes** for strings
- **2 spaces** for indentation
- **camelCase** for variables/functions
- **PascalCase** for React components

```javascript
// Good
const fetchBlogData = async () => {
  const response = await api.getBlogs()
  return response.data
}

// Bad - semicolons, double quotes, wrong indentation
const fetchBlogData = async () => {
    const response = await api.getBlogs();
    return response.data;
};
```

## Technology Constraints

**Never use:**
- TypeScript (`.ts`, `.tsx` files)
- Class components in React
- CSS-in-JS libraries (styled-components, emotion)
- Any UI library other than Ant Design
- Bare color values (hex, rgb, hsl)
- Bare spacing values (custom px/rem values)

**Always use:**
- Modern JavaScript (ES6+)
- Functional React components with hooks
- Ant Design components exclusively
- Ant Design theme tokens for all colors and spacing

## Ant Design Theme Tokens

**Critical:** Always use `theme.useToken()` for dynamic values.

```javascript
import { theme } from 'antd'

function MyComponent() {
  const { token } = theme.useToken()
  
  // Good - using theme tokens
  return (
    <div style={{
      color: token.colorPrimary,
      backgroundColor: token.colorBgContainer,
      padding: token.paddingLG,
      marginBottom: token.marginXL
    }}>
      Content
    </div>
  )
}

// Bad - bare color and spacing values
<div style={{
  color: '#fa541c',
  backgroundColor: '#fff',
  padding: '24px',
  marginBottom: '32px'
}}>
```

## Error Handling

Always use try-catch for async operations with early returns.

```javascript
// Good
const handleSubmit = async (data) => {
  if (!data.title) {
    toast.error('Title is required')
    return
  }

  try {
    await api.createBlog(data)
    toast.success('Blog created!')
  } catch (error) {
    toast.error(error.message || 'Failed to create blog')
  }
}

// Bad - no error handling
const handleSubmit = async (data) => {
  await api.createBlog(data)
}
```

## Performance

Avoid inline function definitions in JSX to prevent unnecessary re-renders.

```javascript
// Good - memoized callback
const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
  doSomething()
}, [doSomething])

return <Button onClick={handleClick}>Click</Button>

// Bad - creates new function on every render
return <Button onClick={() => doSomething()}>Click</Button>
```

